IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF JENKINS LIVING CENTER, INC. IS TO PROVIDE SENIOR HEALTH CARE, HOUSING, AND REHABILITATION SERVICES THAT PROVIDE A HIGH QUALITY OF LIFE TO THE PEOPLE WE SERVE.
IRS990.Desc: JENKINS LIVING CENTER (NURSING HOME OPERATION) - WHEN THE FISCAL YEAR BEGAN ON APRIL 1, 2022, THE FACILITY WAS STILL DEALING WITH THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC. THIS CREATED A LOW RESIDENT CENSUS AS THE AVERAGE OF 89.9. ALONG WITH THE LOW CENSUS, A SHORTAGE OF NURSING STAFF CAUSED THE FACILITY TO RELY ON AGENCY STAFFING. THE COMBINATION OF THE TWO ISSUES IS THE LARGEST FINANCIAL DIFFICULTY AND COSTS THE FACILITY DRASTICALLY. WITH NO FURTHER RELIEF FUNDS DISTRIBUTED IN THE LAST FISCAL YEAR, THE FACILITY HAS SUFFERED A MAJOR LOSS. THE NURSING HOME OPERATION EXPERIENCED A LOSS OF $1,533,368. THE YEAR-TO-DATE PAYER MIX INCLUDED 55% MEDICAID, 37% PRIVATE PAY, AND 8% MEDICARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: JENKINS TOWN VIEW APARTMENTS - THIS HUD-SUBSIDIZED 60-UNIT APARTMENT BUILDING DID NOT SEE THE DECLINE IN OCCUPANCY THAT WAS EXPERIENCED BY THE NURSING HOME AND CONGREGATE LIVING BUILDINGS, THEREFORE REVENUES STAYED STEADY. THE TOWN VIEW APARTMENTS HAVE BEEN AT FULL CAPACITY FOR MOST OF THE TIME AND HAD STEADY PROFITS THROUGHOUT THE YEAR. THE NET PROFIT FOR THE FISCAL YEAR WAS $232,458.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: 200 MAPLE PLACE - THE OCCUPANCY AT THIS 36-APARTMENT CONGREGATE LIVING BUILDING WAS IMPACTED BY COVID-19 BUT STARTED TO SEE A TURNAROUND IN THE ASPECT OF OCCUPANCY. A PROJECT STARTED THIS YEAR TO RENOVATE EACH APARTMENT THROUGHOUT THE BUILDING. THIS CAN ONLY HAPPEN WHEN A PREVIOUS RESIDENT MOVES OUT. THE RENOVATION IS STARTED AND DEPENDENT ON AVAILABLE MAINTENANCE STAFF TO DETERMINE WHEN THE APARTMENTS CAN BE COMPLETED. SOME APARTMENTS HAD A KITCHEN LAYOUT THAT WAS NOT CONDUCIVE TO MOBILITY, ESPECIALLY WITH A WALKER. THIS HAD A LARGER FINANCIAL BURDEN WITH MAJOR RENOVATIONS HAPPENING. THIS LED TO LESS OCCUPANCY DURING RENOVATIONS AND THE COST OF RENOVATIONS. 200 MAPLE PLACE EXPERIENCED A LOSS OF $18,087.

OtherSecuritiesGrp.Desc: INTEREST IN NET ASSETS JENKINS LIVING CENTER FOUNDATION

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CENTER BELIEVES THAT IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN AFFECTING ITS ANNUAL FILING REQUIREMENTS, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE CENTER WILL RECOGNIZE FUTURE ACCRUED INTEREST AND PENALTIES RELATED TO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS AND LIABILITIES IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE IF SUCH INTEREST AND PENALTIES ARE INCURRED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE HAS THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BOARD IF NEEDED. THE COMMITTEE IS COMPRISED OF THE FOUR OFFICER POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CEO/PRESIDENT OF THE ORGANIZATION WILL REVIEW FORM 990. AFTER HIS REVIEW, THE 990 WILL BE PROVIDED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE 990 WILL BE PRESENTED AT A BOARD MEETING AND BOARD MEMBER COMMENTS WILL BE DISCUSSED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, HOWEVER DID UTILIZE A DISCLOSURE FORM WITH THE BOARD MEMBERS AND OFFICERS TO RECOGNIZE ANY REPORTABLE FAMILY OR BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS ON THE 990.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION USES COMPARABILITY DATA WHEN DETERMINING EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION. IN ADDITION, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ESTABLISHES AND ANNUALLY REVIEWS THE SALARY OF THE PRESIDENT/CEO. ALL OTHER SALARIES ARE ESTABLISHED BY ADMINISTRATION AND ARE REVIEWED BY THE BOARD AS PART OF THE OVERALL BUDGET REVIEW PROCESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
